    "html": "<section class=\"catalog-card-content\" data-source-type=\"Review/Preview\">\n<div class=\"problem-body\">\n<p>The diagrams below represent piles of pennies.</p>\n<ol class=\"alpha\">\n<li>Which pile has more pennies? Explain your reasoning.</li>\n<li>Write two different numerical expressions to represent the number of pennies in each pile.</li>\n<li>Write a number comparison statement using $&gt;$, $&lt;$, or $=$ to show if the number of pennies in one pile is greater than the other or if they are the same.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"image-row\"><img alt=\"Pile 1 diagram with six boxes labeled 12, one box labeled 6, and three individual circles.\" src=\"assets/lesson_1_2_2/cc1_1_2_2_1-58_pile_1.png\"/><img alt=\"Pile 2 diagram with sixteen rectangles labeled 5.\" src=\"assets/lesson_1_2_2/cc1_1_2_2_1-58_pile_2.png\"/></div>\n</div>\n</section>",
